<figureCitation box="[710,816,1300,1326]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStartId-0="1.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionStartId-1="3.[136,229,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox-0="[228,1358,195,1915]" captionTargetBox-1="[259,1329,407,1898]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@1.[218,1369,187,1925]" captionTargetId-1="figure-110@3.[235,1353,389,1920]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Maerua koratensis in its natural habitat.A. Flowering branches. B. Fruiting branches." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Maerua koratensis. A. Flowering branch showing flower buds, opened flowers and fully mature flowers. B. Single flower with sepals, petals and the majority of stamens removed; the stamens are situated on a torus elevated on an androgynophore which is concealed by a receptacle. C. Petals; left ventral side and right dorsal side. D. Sepals, left ventral side and right dorsal side. E. Receptacle. F. Fruits." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424254" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424256" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5424254/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5424256/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="215">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
