<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,374,400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Srisanga &amp; Watthana" authorityYear="2021" box="[294,505,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" genus="Maerua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis box="[294,505,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Maerua koratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. juncea" box="[654,928,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" genus="Maerua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="juncea" subSpecies="juncea">
<emphasis box="[654,767,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">M. juncea</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[853,928,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">juncea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having petaliferous flowers with distinct 4- lobed laciniate disc and a similar number of stamens (
<bibRefCitation author="Killick, D. J. B." box="[750,896,410,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" pagination="39 - 42" refId="ref3477" refString="Killick, D. J. B. (1969) The disc in the Southern African species of Maerua. Bothalia 10: 39 - 42. https: // doi. org / 10.4102 / abc. v 10 i 1.1507" type="journal article" year="1969">Killick 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Abreu, J. A. &amp; Martins, E. S. &amp; Catarino, L." box="[907,1110,410,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" pagination="19 - 25" refId="ref2686" refString="Abreu, J. A., Martins, E. S. &amp; Catarino, L. (2014) New species of Maerua (Capparaceae) from Angola. Blumea 59: 19 - 25. https: // doi. org / 10.3767 / 000651914 X 681964" type="journal article" year="2014">
Abreu 
<emphasis box="[985,1043,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hyde, M. A. &amp; Wursten, B. T. &amp; Ballings, P. &amp; Coates Palgrave, M." box="[1122,1315,410,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" refId="ref3153" refString="Hyde, M. A., Wursten, B. T., Ballings, P. &amp; Coates Palgrave, M. (2019) Flora of Zimbabwe: Species information: Maerua juncea subsp. juncea. Available from: https: // www. zimbabweflora. co. zw / speciesdata / species. php? species _ id = 124630 (accessed 6 June 2019)" type="url" year="2019">
Hyde 
<emphasis box="[1191,1248,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
, PROTA4U 2019), but can be distinguished as outlined in the diagnosis and 
<tableCitation box="[853,936,446,472]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,556,580]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of morphological characters between Maerua koratensis and M. juncea subsp. juncea." pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Srisanga &amp; Watthana" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,399,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" genus="Maerua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="koratensis">
<emphasis box="[189,399,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="218">Maerua koratensis</emphasis>
